files.name: Cargo.toml
files.content:
[workspace]
resolver = "2"
members = [
    "code/wasm-builder",

    # beginner tutorials
    "code/beginner/*",

    # intermediate tutorials
    "code/intermediate/*",

    # showcase
    "code/showcase/*",

    "run-wasm",
]
exclude = [
    "code/showcase/imgui-demo",
    "code/showcase/pong",
]

files.name: FEATURES.md
files.content:
# Features

## Planned
* Framebuffer
* code download links

## Things I'd like
* Screen shots
* Create gifs of examples running (?)
* Displaying random models as wireframe and solid

files.name: index.template.html
files.content:
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
</head>

<body>
    <!-- 
        This is adapted from https://github.com/gfx-rs/wgpu/blob/master/run-wasm-example.sh 
        
        Eventually I'll have all the examples create there own components for vuepress to
        use, but this will do for now.
    -->
    <script type="module">
        import init from "./pong.js";
        window.addEventListener("load", () => {
            init();
        });
    </script>
</body>

</html>

package.json
run-all.sh
files.content:
#!/bin/bash

(trap 'kill 0' SIGINT;
cargo run --bin tutorial1-window &
cargo run --bin tutorial2-surface &
cargo run --bin tutorial2-challenge &
cargo run --bin tutorial3-pipeline &
cargo run --bin tutorial3-challenge &
cargo run --bin tutorial4-buffer &
cargo run --bin tutorial4-challenge &
cargo run --bin tutorial5-textures &
cargo run --bin tutorial5-challenge &
cargo run --bin tutorial6-uniforms &
cargo run --bin tutorial6-challenge &
cargo run --bin tutorial7-instancing &
cargo run --bin tutorial7-challenge &
cargo run --bin tutorial8-depth &
cargo run --bin tutorial8-challenge &
cargo run --bin tutorial9-models &
cargo run --bin tutorial10-lighting &
cargo run --bin tutorial11-normals &
cargo run --bin tutorial12-camera &
cargo run --bin tutorial13-hdr &
cargo run --bin windowless &
cargo run --bin gifs &
cargo run --bin compute
# cargo run --bin pong
)
